    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-03-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-03-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1096"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1096">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-03-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 99.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reference to the disaster to the United States
                    ship of war <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi>, I have the honor to report that all of
                    the foreign ministers have taken occasion to express their sense of regret and
                    sorrow to me <pb facs="1174" n="1078" xml:id="pg_1078"/> in a very earnest,
                    sincere, and satisfactory way, save the ministers of Italy and Spain, who have
                    said nothing.</p>
                <p>The English and German ministers called personally at the legation within two or
                    three hours after the news of the loss of the <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi> was
                    confirmed.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis B. Loomis.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
